AGI - "With the entry of Slovenia into the European Union, twenty years ago, our countries reunited in a shared path: and the Italian Republic was pleased to be able to support and accompany the process of accession, so that the two peoples found themselves to contribute to a common destiny". It is a passage from the speech of the President of the Republic, Sergio Mattarella, at the inauguration ceremony of the "First European Capital of Cross-border Culture Go2025!>".
&nbsp;
"By working side by side in the European institutions - the head of the State emphasizes - mutual trust has been consolidated and there has matured sense of belonging and a further identity: the common European identity. The differences, the misunderstandings, have left the place to factors that unite. This expresses the great historical value of European integration."
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"Nova Gorica and Gorizia love to celebrate the culture of borders. With Chemnitz, in Germany, Nova Gorica was chosen as the European capital of 2025 culture and the Slovenian city wanted to launch with the twin Gorizia a challenge: to propose itself as an experience of culture through the frontier", he adds.> "If culture, by definition, knows no boundaries, it is born, but always, as an expression of a community but open to knowledge, to common research, to mutual enrichment. The horrors of nationalist extremism, which has so badly produced in Europe - the head of the State notes - emerge the values of cohabitation and acceptance. These are the values that can oppose the obscurantism of war and conflict that has been reproposed with Russian aggression against Ukraine."
